<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12056b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12056b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12056b"> 56(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> chronogram / 1425 MCCCLLVVVVIIIII / 15 letters / 7 words / Maclovii pardis dat vulnera / cancer in vadis</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">106-7: La plupart des auteurs assignent &agrave; cet engagement naval la date de l423. Ils r&eacute;p&egrave;tent l&apos;erreur commise par d&apos;Argentr&eacute;, Dom Lobineau, Dom Th. le Roy, Baud, etc., alors qu&apos;il est certain que ce combat fut livr&eacute; entre le 20 juin et le 9 juillet 1425. Le texte m&ecirc;me de la Chronique du Mont l&apos;indique nettement: &laquo;L&apos;an mil quatorze cent vingt-cinq, les dits Anglois mirent derechief si&egrave;ge &agrave; la mer devant le dict Mont, &agrave; grande force de navirez, des quieulz Lorens Hauldain estoit cappitaine qui furent combattu par Monseigneur d&apos;Auzebosc, Monseigneur de Beaufort, les bourgeois de Saint-Malou et plusieurs aultres cheva-<font color="green">[106]</font> liers et escuiers et aultres.&raquo; Le paragraphe se termine ainsi: Ma CloV II PardIs, dat Vvulnera CanCer In Vadis. (Maclovii pardis dat vulnera cancer in vadis.) Ce vers, qui constitue un v&eacute;ritable chronogramme, d&eacute;montre bien que rengagement se produisit, en juin; le Cancer, signe du Zodiaque correspondant &agrave; ce mois. Il contient, en effet Un M = 1,000 / Trois C = 3 x 100 = 300 / Deux L = 50 + 50 = 100 / Quatre V = 5 x 4 = 20 / Cinq I = 5 x 1 = 5 / Total&hellip; 1.425 <br>[Most authors place this naval battle in 1234. They repeat the error committed by d&apos;Argentr&eacute;, Dom Lobineau, Dom Th. le Roy, Baud, etc., while it is certain that the battle took place between 20 June and 9 July 1425. The text itself of the Chronicle of the Mont says so explicitly: &ldquo;In the year 1425, the aforementioned English laid siege via the sea in front of the Mon, with a great force of ships, of which Lorens Hauldain was captain and they were conquered by Monseigneur d&apos;Auzebosc, Monseigneur de Beaufort, the inhabitants of Saint-Malo and numerous knights and squires and others. The paragraph ends like this: <br>Ma CloV II PardIs, dat Vvulnera CanCer In Vadis. (Maclovii pardis dat vulnera cancer in vadis.) <br>One M = 1.000 / Three C = 3 x 100 = 300 / Two L = 50 + 50 = 100 / Four V = 5 x 4 = 20 / Five I = 5 x 1 = 5 / Total&hellip; 1.425 <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="SMIN" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SMIN"><cite title="source">Le Mont Saint-Michel Inconnu</cite></a> (1912) 106-7</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The Latin motto translates as: In shallow waters, the crab of Saint-Malo wounds the [English] leopards. </mm> </dd></dl>
